ZH: 他的成绩在班上名列前茅。
EN: His grades rank top in the class.

ZH: 她的成绩比以前有所提高。
EN: Her grades have improved compared to before.

ZH: 我们需要努力来取得好成绩。
EN: We need to work hard to achieve good grades.

ZH: 他的成绩不太理想，需要努力加油。
EN: His grades are not very ideal and he needs to work harder.

ZH: 她得到了很高的成绩，让家人感到骄傲。
EN: She achieved very high grades, making her family proud.

ZH: 这次考试成绩出乎意料地好。
EN: The results of this exam were unexpectedly good.

ZH: 老师们会时不时地公布我们的成绩。
EN: Teachers will occasionally announce our grades.

ZH: 考试成绩的好坏并不代表一切。
EN: Exam grades do not represent everything.

ZH: 我很满意我的这次考试成绩。
EN: I am very satisfied with my exam results.

ZH: 她每次都能拿到最高分成绩。
EN: She always gets the highest grades.

ZH: 她的高考成绩决定了她能否上理想的大学。
EN: Her college entrance exam scores determine if she can go to her ideal university.

ZH: 我们应该把成绩作为前进的动力。
EN: We should use our grades as motivation to move forward.

ZH: 某些人过于关注成绩，而忽略了学习的乐趣。
EN: Some people focus too much on grades and neglect the joy of learning.

ZH: 他花了很多时间和精力才取得这么好的成绩。
EN: He spent a lot of time and effort to achieve such good grades.

ZH: 这个学生虽然成绩不错，但是懒惰。
EN: This student has good grades, but is lazy.

ZH: 她每次都能保持优秀的成绩。
EN: She always maintains excellent grades.

ZH: 考试成绩是评判学习效果的一个重要指标。
EN: Exam results are an important indicator of learning outcomes.

ZH: 成绩优秀并不代表就一定能成功。
EN: Excellent grades do not necessarily guarantee success.

ZH: 这次期末考试的成绩将决定升级的结果。
EN: The final exam results will determine the promotion outcome.

ZH: 他为了争取好成绩而日夜兼程地学习。
EN: He studies day and night in order to strive for good grades.
